	 <h1><a name="essay">Long Story Short</a></h1>
<p>	 
The best antenna to start with would be a cloverleaf antenna on your receiver and a skew planar antenna on your
video transmitter because you don't know any better.</p> 
<p>
Let's change that!</p>
<p>
Some FPV kits already include these antennas, but if not most vendors sell them as a pair of
FPV antennas. These are Omni directional, circular polarized antennas which work relay well for FPV.
Generally price gives a good indication on the quality and precision of the antenna. When comparing the same
type of antenna from different manufactures, the expensive one will usually have better range. This is
because they are made using better materials, and with further precision.
</p>
However, that is not always the case and
it’s up to you if you think it is worth to pay double to get a 10% increase in range.
As you become familiar with FPV flying and you desire further range you can upgrade to more directional
systems such as a helical antenna.
